{
  "name": "microsoft-s-move-to-mothball-old-code-ra-724d34",
  "title": "Microsoft's Move To Mothball Old Code Raises Concerns",
  "description": "Datamation/EarthWeb article on Microsoft's announcement that it will retire pre-Windows NT 32-bit legacy code (Windows 9x / Windows 95) rather than continue patching vulnerabilities. Peter Kastner (Aberdeen Group CRO) endorses the decision \u2014 Microsoft has to make this call to stay true to its 'fix security-prone code' mantra \u2014 while noting the collateral pain for the tens of millions still on Windows 9x/95. IDC's Dan Kusnetzky offers contrasting nuance.",
